# Go Conventions (Go 1.26+)

## stdlib-first

- HTTP routing: `net/http` with Go 1.22+ method patterns (`mux.HandleFunc("GET /v1/health", h)`)
- Logging: `log/slog` structured logger, pass `*slog.Logger` via constructor
- Errors: `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)` wrapping, `errors.Is` / `errors.As` for checking
- Testing: stdlib `testing`, table-driven tests, `t.Parallel()`, `t.Context()`, `testing/synctest`
- JSON: `encoding/json`, use struct tags
- Dev tools: `go tool golangci-lint run`, `go tool air` -- tracked via `tool` directive in go.mod

## Go 1.24-1.26 Idioms

```go
// sync.WaitGroup.Go (Go 1.25+) -- spawn tracked goroutines
var wg sync.WaitGroup
wg.Go(func() {
    e.flushMemTable(ctx)
})
wg.Wait()

// new(expr) (Go 1.26) -- pointer-to-value initialization
optionalField := new("default value")  // *string pointing to "default value"

// t.Context() (Go 1.24+) -- auto-canceled on test cleanup
func TestEngine_Put(t *testing.T) {
    ctx := t.Context()
    engine := setupTestEngine(t)
    err := engine.Put(ctx, []byte("key"), []byte("val"))
    // ctx is canceled when test ends
}

// testing/synctest (Go 1.25+) -- deterministic concurrent tests
func TestCompaction(t *testing.T) {
    synctest.Run(func() {
        engine := setupTestEngine(t)
        // trigger compaction...
        synctest.Wait() // waits until all goroutines block
        // assert compaction results
    })
}
```

## Patterns

```go
// Constructor injection -- no globals, no init()
func NewEngine(cfg Config, log *slog.Logger) (*Engine, error) {
    // validate cfg, return initialized struct
}

// Interface at the consumer, not the producer
type Searcher interface {
    Search(ctx context.Context, query string, opts SearchOpts) ([]Result, error)
}

// Table-driven tests
func TestEngine_Get(t *testing.T) {
    t.Parallel()
    ctx := t.Context()
    tests := []struct{
        name string
        key  string
        want string
        err  error
    }{
        {name: "found", key: "k1", want: "v1"},
        {name: "missing", key: "none", err: ErrNotFound},
    }
    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {
            t.Parallel()
            // use ctx ...
        })
    }
}
```

## Naming

- No package-name stutter: `storage.Engine` not `storage.StorageEngine`
- Acronyms: `ID`, `HTTP`, `URL` (all caps), not `Id`, `Http`
- Unexported helpers: keep small, colocate with caller
- File per concern: `wal.go`, `wal_test.go` -- not multi-thousand-line files
